<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Check EC2 instances connectivity</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 1 minute to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><br>
To connect the master or worker node, you need to connect the bastion instance launched in the public subnet firstly using SSH and then connect from the bastion instance to other instances launched in the private subnet.<br><br>
To connect the bastion node, follow these steps:<br>
</p>
<ol>
<li>Open the Amazon EC2 console at <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/</a>.<br></li>
<li>Choose your bastion instance.<br></li>
<li>Click <b>Connect</b>. <br></li>
<li>Follow the on-screen instructions to make the connection.<br></li>
</ol>
<p>To connect the master or worker node, follow these steps:<br>
</p>
<ol>
<li>Connect the bastion instance first, as described above.<br></li>
<li>Open the Amazon EC2 console at <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/</a>.<br></li>
<li>Choose your node.<br></li>
<li>Click <b>Connect</b>. </li>
<li>Follow the on-screen instructions to connect from bastion instance to other instances.<br></li>
</ol>

